##Jang dinh-woo, a patient's rebellion

Micro Signal Zhenshigushi1

Function description, every day a moving original true story.

Zhang dingyu often says, oneself"too hasty". His sense of urgency, coming from his own dwindling motor neurons and from the COVID-19, which has ravaged Wuhan, is to snatch more lives from the hands of death.

Zhang dingyu was in a hurry. On the day he was filmed on national television, he shuffled past clinic halls, wards, duty rooms, conference rooms and CT rooms. When talking to doctors and nurses, they talk very fast. A nurse lost his temper in public after performing a procedure that could affect the results of a virus test on a sample.

In the last year or two, the doctors and nurses of the Golden Pool Hospital knew that the director's temper was getting more and more impetuous, and his legs were becoming less agile. Infection Department Director Wen danning recalled, Zhang dingyu walking uneven feet, up and down the stairs always grasp the handrails, movement difficulties. She asked many times, and he just said "knee surgery. ".

Wait until this epidemic, Zhang Dingyu had no choice but to confess his illness, he suffered from "als" , leg muscles are gradually atrophy, necrosis.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Image | from CCTV

The arrival of new coronary pneumonia, the acute dean of the hospital even more urgent. "The whole hospital knows that I have a quick temper and a loud voice. " After 34 years in medicine, Zhang Dingyu has become an authority on infectious diseases in Wuhan.

On December 29,2019, the first batch of seven patients with pneumonia of unknown cause were admitted to Jinyintan hospital. Medical staff did throat swabs for the patient and found that the results were negative, but the lung CT showed abnormalities, lung spots increased, and the patient's condition continued to deteriorate. They suspect the virus travels through the Lower Airways into the Alveoli, and the throat exam doesn't work.

The next morning, Zhang dingyu emergency decision: strengthen disinfection protection, vacate isolation ward, transfer other patients, deployment of hospital medical resources. At the same time, medical staff collected the Bronchoalveolar lavage fluid of seven patients and sent it to Wuhan Virus Institute of Chinese Academy of Sciences for testing.

Four days later, the hospital opened an isolation ward for unidentified pneumonia cases.

Zhang dingyu's fierce action once brought a lot of pressure to colleagues. Zhang, they recall, often arrived earlier than his shift-changing colleagues, asking about the number of patients admitted that day, the number of patients transferred that day. A doctor to the hospital director to call the new ward shortage of manpower, Zhang Dingyu immediately with the nursing department, Logistics Department to the scene coordination. South Three Ward Director Zhang Li concluded, "(this time) urgent task layout, high requirements, no matter how small, scold people without mercy. "

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Image | from CCTV

In retrospect, she said, "it was thanks to his temper and his decisiveness. "

On Jan. 7, a team at the Chinese Center for Disease Control and Prevention separated samples collected by Zhang and colleagues. On January 8, the National Commission of Health announced that the initial confirmation of the "COVID-19" for the cause of the epidemic.

Then the outbreak broke out in Wuhan.

As a Special Medical Institution for Infectious Diseases, Jinyintan hospital is also the first designated hospital opened in Wuhan. During the Spring Festival, the number of referrals from other hospitals increased dramatically, and the 14-bed ICU was a drop in the bucket. Zhang Dingyu put the focus on opening a new ICU ward, try to admit more patients.

After more than 20 days of hard work, on January 24, at 8 p.m. on New Year's Eve, Zhang Dingyu received a call from the Wuhan Municipal Health and Health Commission. He was told that 316 medical staff from Shanghai would arrive in Wuhan by special plane at 2 a.m. and enter Jinyintan Hospital.

The next day, the Army Medical University medical team took over the two areas of the Golden Pool, responsible for the treatment of 20 confirmed patients. Shanghai medical team officially took over the Golden Pool Hospital Old Ward, a total of 2 wards, 80 beds. As of that day, a total of 657 patients were admitted to the hospital.

Professor Chen Dechang, a specialist in critical care medicine in Shanghai Ruijin Hospital, carried out ECMO in his ward for the first time, and achieved good results. Zheng Junhua, vice president of Shanghai First People's Hospital, deployed medical staff efficiently and led the medical team to work quickly in an unfamiliar environment. With the help of the Shanghai experts, Zhang dingyu settled down a little, grateful and admiring.

These from Shanghai, Beijing's medical experts team, many of his long-respected industry predecessors. Zhang dingyu walks inconveniently, often can not receive personally, the heart has the guilt. Soon after, he decided to come clean and was diagnosed with motor neurone disease, also known as als. It is a rare and incurable disease for which there is no known cure. The patient will develop muscle atrophy and deglutition difficulty slowly, produce breath exhaustion and die.

"I'm in a hurry because I don't have much time left in my life. " As early as October 2018, Zhang dingyu was diagnosed with als. As a doctor, he knew exactly what was coming for him, and the disease was the end of his life ahead of time.

He knew that as his body's muscle cells gradually atrophied, his tall body would shrink into a tiny mass, trapped first in a wheelchair and then in bed, communicating with others by blinking, using a breathing machine to create tubes in his stomach, he ends up dying of respiratory failure. Every als patient watches himself die like this.

With less and less time left, Zhang decided to do something about it. He chose not to share the news of his illness with his colleagues, who did not know it but felt that the dean's temper had grown increasingly impatient over the course of time and that he could not afford to be careless about his work.

In 2007 and 2011, Zhang Dingyu accompanied Chinese medical teams to Algeria and Pakistan to carry out international medical assistance. On May 14,2008, three days after the Sichuan earthquake, Zhang Dingyu, as the head of the Hubei Province's third medical team, appeared in the hard hit area of Shifang to try his best to treat the injured.

The COVID-19 attack is the biggest challenge facing Zhang since he began his career. His body was overwhelmed by the constant overload of work. In an interview, he revealed that he had felt his gluteus maximus muscles atrophy in the last two to three months. At night, he could clearly feel the space between his joint capsule and his joints. The muscle cells are shrinking faster than they thought.

In an interview with face-to-face, the ALS director was surprisingly upbeat and forthright, anticipating that he would be confined to a wheelchair, doing more now and perhaps having fewer regrets later.

He said: "Everyone's destination is death, and I just know that my destination may not be too far away, so I want to use this time, use it well, not the same can do something else? "

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Image | Zhang Dingyu in CCTV-13, face to face

On January 14, Zhang Dingyu's wife, who works at the COVID-19 in Wuhan, was diagnosed with COVID-19. Zhang Dingyu, who had always been calm, suddenly panicked. In the evening, on the drive to visit his wife, Zhang dingyu cried.

For 28 years, that was the most frightening night for Zhang Dingyu. Sitting in the isolation ward, Zhang dingyu chatted with his wife for a while. Zhang dingyu was in pain as he watched her hobble and frazzle.

Over the next three or four days, as the number of patients at the hospital grew, Zhang was too busy to visit his wife. He felt so guilty that he said in a later interview: "I may be a good doctor, but I'm not a good husband. "

Soon after, the good news came that she was doing better with antiviral drug. On January 29, she was discharged from the hospital and sent home to recuperate.

On February 3, the Wuhan Bureau of Human Resources and Social Security issued a notice to commend Zhang Dingyu for his outstanding deeds and decided to award him a meritorious record.

On Feb. 6, the Government of the People's Republic of China decided to award him a major honor.

February 9, the 15th day of the Lunar Calendar. On CCTV's Lantern Festival special, host Shui Junyi connects with doctor Zhang Dingyu who is on the front line. On the left breast of the white coat, Zhang dingyu pinned a party emblem. He said that thanks to the people of the country, I used to sleep three hours a day, now I can sleep six hours, "thank you very much, my sleep is given by the people of the country. "

As of the evening of the 10th, with the efforts of Wuhan's Golden Pool Hospital and medical staff from all over Wuhan, the hospital has treated more than 1,500 patients, and some patients have been discharged smoothly. A total of 9 staff members were found to have nosocomial infection in the hospital. Some of them have been discharged and no serious cases have been reported. This and Zhang dingyu early sharp, vigorous and resolute action is not unrelated.

At 1 a.m. on Feb. 4, Zhang Dingyu went to the living room shelter hospital in Wuhan to check on the preparations. In a video posted by a netizen, he hobbles along, leaving people in a hurry behind.
